SUID: for files
    s replases x in owner user.
    -rwsr-xr-x file
    1. SUID only works at binary program
    2. executor must have x right at this file
    3. only works in run-time
    4. executor will get owner user's right
    
SGID: for files and directory
    



SBIT:  for directory
    1. only root and direcotry creator can remove this directory, others only modify
    


how to set:
    4:SUID
    2:SGID
    1:SBIT
    
    chmod 4755 filename ->  -rwsr-xr-x
    chmod 2555 filename ->  -r-xr-sr-x
    
文件或目录必须先有执行权限，然后赋予的SUID、SGID、SBIT才能起作用
如果不具有执行权限，配置后的标志为S和T。




















